docker allows you to map a differnt port to your localhosts container port 
-p is the flag needed to map a port to localhosts container port

docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx:latest

you can also map multiple ports to your localhosts container port

docker run -d -p 8080:80 -p 3000:80 nginx:latest ====== will allow both 8080 and 3000 to map to your localhosts container port
